---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Report Review & Next-Step Planning | Rabbia Ashraf NeuroCare Child Development Services"
  description="Rabbia Ashraf NeuroCare helps parents understand school, developmental, therapy, ASD, ADHD, psychological, or learning reports and turn recommendations into practical next steps."
>
  <div class="bg-brand-cream py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Understand the Report. Plan the Next Step.</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Many parents receive reports filled with terms, scores, recommendations, and referrals but still feel unsure what to do next. Rabbia Ashraf NeuroCare helps parents understand the report and prepare a practical support plan.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl space-y-12">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">What reports can be reviewed</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">We review psychological assessments, occupational or speech therapy evaluations, IEPs, school progress reports, and ASD/ADHD diagnostic reports to help you understand the findings.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">What parents often feel confused about</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Clinical jargon, percentile scores, diagnostic criteria, and extensive lists of generic recommendations can be overwhelming. We break these down into plain language.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">What a report review session may include</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">A structured walkthrough of the report, highlighting key strengths and challenges, clarifying the diagnoses or findings, and prioritizing the recommendations.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Questions to ask after receiving a report</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">We guide you on what to ask the evaluating professional, your child's school, or prospective therapists based on the report's contents.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">How this connects to school, home, and therapy support</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">We help translate the report's findings into actionable goals for the classroom, practical strategies for home routines, and focused objectives for future therapies.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Service Boundaries</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Report review sessions provide psychoeducational guidance and planning support. We do not provide second opinions on medical diagnoses, alter official reports, or guarantee specific service eligibility.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/book" class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-brand-navy text-white rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-blue-900 transition-all shadow-lg">
          Book Consultation
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
